def_en: You use nominal to indicate that someone or something is supposed to have a particular identity or status, but in reality does not have it.

def_cn: (价格或款项)微不足道的，象征性的
def_en: A nominal price or sum of money is very small in comparison with the real cost or value of the thing that is being bought or sold.

def_cn: (价值、比率或水平)名义的
def_en: In economics, the nominal value, rate, or level of something is the one expressed in terms of current prices or figures, without taking into account general changes in prices that take place over time.
